entry.title: Ukraine Fires on Bridges, Rail Lines, to Disrupt Russian Defense of Kherson
entry.content: Ukrainian forces struck a railway bridge in the southern Kherson region, the Ukrainian military said, as it seeks to cut Moscow’s supply lines in preparation for a looming counter-offensive.

entry.title: For Stricken Lebanon, Shipments of Ukrainian Grain Might Not Be Enough
entry.content: The first cargo of grain to leave Ukraine’s key Black Sea ports since the Russian invasion is expected to dock this week in Lebanon, the country where food inflation is the highest in the world.
